"Abstract We are coming to the end of our 15-month odyssey into end-to-end Digital Investigation (EEDI). Over that period we have seen how a digital investigation has some characteristics that make it unique from other types of investigation, and some that are similar to traditional investigative work. We have tried to separate digital forensics from digital investigation, explored a process language for describing an incident in detail, completed an incident post-mortem (or, more correctly, a post-incident root cause analysis) and discussed how EEDI can help us figure out what actually happened."
